generations.rag:
The Court uses the following criteria to determine whether a criminal proceeding, where hearsay evidence is used against a defendant and conducted in accordance with Article 6 §§ 1 and 3 (d) of the Convention:
(i) Whether the accused has been given an adequate opportunity at any stage during earlier proceedings or trial to question persons whose statements are introduced into the case [001-149566];
(ii) Where such questioning was not possible when making their initial statement nor later on, if these statements form either solely or decisively contribute towards conviction by the court. In this scenario, it may be determined that the rights of defense have potentially been restricted beyond what can reasonably comply with guarantees provided under Article 6[Al Khawaja & Tahery v Moldova and Russia, Application no. 2873/02].
